      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. Line the baking tray with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub in the butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{self-raising-flour}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{baking-powder}} in a large bowl. Add the cold cubed {{unsalted-butter}} and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "rub in",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp5nk2ib0000zkv4v35ycyaf"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " with cool fingertips until the mixture looks like fine breadcrumbs with no visible pieces of butter. Stir in the {{caster-sugar}} and {{sultanas}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring together, eight strokes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a well in the centre and pour in the cold {{buttermilk}}. Use a palette knife or a flat butter knife to bring the dough together with cutting strokes, not stirring. Stop the moment there are no dry patches. The dough will be shaggy.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pat and cut",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and pat it gently to 2.5 cm thick. Do not roll it repeatedly. Cut rounds with a 5 cm cutter dipped in flour, pressing straight down. Gather the offcuts, pat together once, and cut again. Arrange on the tray close together but not touching.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze and bake, 12 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the tops lightly with beaten egg. Take care not to let the glaze run down the sides, which would seal the layers and prevent the scone from rising evenly. Bake for 11 to 13 minutes, until the tops are deep gold and the scones have risen with a slight split around the middle. They are done when they sound slightly hollow tapped on the base.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cool on the rack for at least 5 minutes before splitting. Serve with clotted cream and jam in whichever order you prefer.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
